{
  "doc_id": "549",
  "text": "In the past few decades, several methods have been adopted and been practiced all over the world for the processing of bauxite residue, numerous publications have demonstrated that the bauxite residue can be used as an adsorbent to sequester carbon dioxide [CITATION_1] , to remove phosphate [CITATION_2] and fluoride (26) from water, and obtained rare earth metals by leaching experiments [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . These methods can solve the problem of cumulative storage of BRM to a certain extent, nevertheless, when bauxite residue was used to reduce environmental pollution, the risks imposed by the BRM itselves cannot be ignored, for example, it may cause secondary pollution.",
